Key Match Events: Lawrence Mulenga produced six impressive saves to keep Zambia in the contest.
Stopilla Sunzu won more duels than any other player on the pitch (9).
Frankie Musonda made the most clearances in the contest (6).
Emmanuel Banda made the most final third passes in the match (11) and had the most shots on target (2).
Post-Match Reflections: Avram Grant praised the quality, passion, and desire shown by the Copper Bullets.
Avram Grant mentioned that Zambia now turns to the FIFA World Cup qualifiers, where a rematch with Morocco awaits in June.
